### Brand Value

with the example of Snapple

Snapple was first distributed through mom-and-pop stores. It has 52 flavors. With itâ€™s personified brand, Snappleâ€™s growth started straight around 1988.

Quaker(which owned Gatorade) bought Snapple and destroyed the brand value (1.4 Billion of value) Itâ€™s the example of misunderstanding what a brand means to the consumer. 

